Michael and Anthony ANZALONE, v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7932. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 29, 1938. Henry Lavine, of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellants. E. B. Freed, U. S. Atty., of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, ALLEN, and HAMILTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
